  "decision": "Accepted",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Uncertainty quantification was performed via a Monte Carlo propagation of inlet boundary condition variability and blood viscosity uncertainty across the five flow-speed operating points; a screening sensitivity study using one-at-a-time parameter perturbations was conducted internally and informed the UQ input distributions. Results confirm that hemolysis index predictions remain below the RH < 1 acceptance threshold across the sampled uncertainty space.",
