    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels at MRL 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out at MRL 2 with documented justification. The UQ propagation confirms that hemolysis predictions remain within the RH < 1 acceptance criterion across the uncertainty space covering inlet flow rate, blood viscosity, and hemolysis model coefficient variability. The screening sensitivity study conducted during model development informed the selection of UQ input variables and their distributions, providing confidence that the most physically significant inputs were included in the uncertainty propagation. The overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support the regulatory decision for this Class II CPB device at Medium assurance level.",
